         <div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">

<ab><lb n="1"/>  <persName type="emperor"><name nymRef="#Ἀττίνας">Ἀτίαν</name>  <persName type="emperor"><name nymRef="#Βάλβος">Βάλβου</name></persName></persName>  <w lemma="μήτηρ">μητέ<unclear reason="damage">ρα</unclear></w>  <lb n="2"/><persName key="Augustus" type="emperor"><name nymRef="#Σεβαστός"><w lemma="σεβαστός">Σεβαστοῦ</w></name>  <name nymRef="#Καῖσαρ">Καίσαρος</name></persName></ab>
</div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>
               <supplied reason="subaudible">They set up the statue of</supplied>) Atia daughter of Balbus, mother of Augustus Caesar.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Probably one of the Sebasteion group of dedications to the imperial family (<ref type="inscription" n="1315" target="090037.xml"/>=72.224, <ref type="inscription" n="1316" target="090038.xml"/>=72.237, <ref type="inscription" n="1317" target="090039.xml"/>=72.275, <ref type="inscription" n="1318" target="090040.xml"/>=73.145, <ref type="inscription" n="1296" target="090033.xml"/>=77.123, <ref type="inscription" n="1288" target="090026.xml"/>=80.172, <ref type="inscription" n="1289" target="090027.xml"/>=82.108, <ref type="inscription" n="1298" target="090035.xml"/>=82.109, <ref type="inscription" n="1290" target="090028.xml"/>=82.116, <ref type="inscription" n="1297" target="090034.xml"/>=82.117, <ref type="inscription" n="1291" target="090029.xml"/>=82.118, <ref type="inscription" n="1299" target="090036.xml"/>=82.210, <ref type="inscription" n="1293" target="090030.xml"/>=84.30, <ref type="inscription" n="1294" target="090031.xml"/>=84.31, and  <ref type="inscription" n="1295" target="090032.xml"/>=84.41).</p>
            <p>On these see <bibl n="jmr1996b">
                  <author>Reynolds</author> (1996), <title level="a">Ruler-cult at Aphrodisias</title>
               </bibl>.</p>
         </div>
